begin_memory_text: We talked about where we live and where we are from and what our towns are like. I am in NC and she is in New Jersey so we just discussed that for a bit
middle_memory_text: We talked about school. She was supposed to be at college but she is not so we talked about her tutoring in her town and how it is that she gets clients
end_memory_text: Towards the end we talked about not wanting to work and wanting to be able to live a life where all of our bills would be paid and we could just do what we wanted
rest_of_day_open: I think the rest of my week is going to be super boring. Basically I have 67 12 page midterms to grade and I am barely being paid ANYTHING to do it, so I will be grading for hours on end and probably complaining about it and getting super frustrated. YAYYY grad school is the best!
critical_positive: I think what worked well is that we found common topics to discuss. We are both students adjusting to virtual learning and we both tutor so it was easy to find common topics to explore. She is also an active listener so it was easy to talk because she was clearly engaged
critical_negative: For the most part it was pretty smooth because we had enough to talk about to fill the time that we were talking for. I think towards the end it was dying down a bit because we were kind of running out of things to say but eventually she said she had to go so that was the end of it

begin_memory_text: We introduced ourselves and talked about what we were doing for school. I am a college undergraduate and she was a grad student getting her PhD. We also talked about what we did for work, we both worked multiple jobs and tutored which was cool. I gave her some tips on independent tutoring .
middle_memory_text: We talked about different things about college and high. My memory is a little fuzzy but I remembering complaining about rich people and some people that I went to high school. The AP and IB programs also came up at some point. We talked about jobs and not wanting to work or be slaves to capitalism.
end_memory_text: We wished each other well and talked about making money off surveys. We also briefly talked about the first conversations we did, mine was with a nice woman and hers was with a man who was quiet but nice and had a bunch of cats and a family horse farm.
rest_of_day_open: It's been okay. It could either go up or go down. Most of my hardest work is behind me and I'm looking forward to relaxing where I can. My boyfriend and I are in a bit of fight right now, so that's not great. I hope we get better rather than exploding.
critical_positive: We both had similar backgrounds and worries/complaints about life so that really worked. I think our core beliefs were in sync and that made conversation really good, combined with a similar age demographic and similar professional wishes. Our sense of humor was the best too, we laughed at the same things.
critical_negative: I can't really think of anything hugely distractive or bad. Sometimes she talked a lot more than I did, and I was worried about getting a word in the discussion, but overall it was not really that bad in retrospect. I often feel that I can get out what i need to say in shorter form anyway.
